## Critical Rules (NEVER VIOLATE)

### Architecture
- **NEVER** mix layers - Each layer has a single responsibility
- **NEVER** import from inner layers in outer layers
- **ALWAYS** use dependency injection

### Error Handling
- **NEVER** use hardcoded error strings
- **ALWAYS** use centralized error handling
- **NEVER** expose internal errors to clients

### Configuration
- **NEVER** hardcode values
- **ALWAYS** use configuration files
- **ALWAYS** validate configuration on startup

### Libraries
- **NEVER** add unapproved libraries
- **ALWAYS** check library-standards.mdc first
- **ALWAYS** use approved library stack

### Security
- **NEVER** implement authentication (use API Gateway)
- **NEVER** implement rate limiting (use API Gateway)
- **ALWAYS** validate all inputs
- **ALWAYS** sanitize user data

